The paper proposes a method for face detection, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). The method involves analyzing and improving upon a baseline single-stage detector, which requires machine learning techniques such as deep neural networks (cs.AI). The paper also discusses strategies for reducing false positives, which is a common problem in machine learning and requires statistical analysis (cs.LG). The proposed method involves leveraging context information from deeper layers, which is a common technique in multimedia processing (cs.MM). Finally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of the proposed method on several face detection benchmarks, which involves analyzing the performance of the method and comparing it to other methods, a common task in cryptography (cs.CR).
